<p><strong>E:</strong> MarketplaceMCI offering business services</p>

<p><strong>P:</strong> Nice looking sites [6]</p>

<p><strong>E:</strong> ‚ÄúMarketplaceMCI sites which Webgen ended up copying as they looked
nice.‚Äù</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Sketch of a business plan for Webgen. 24 Aug 95.</p>

  <p>OVERVIEW</p>

  <p>Webgen allows clients to generate (web catalogs)[1] remotely.</p>

  <p>There are (several other companies that can generate and serve web
catalogs)[2]. The best known site of this type is Marketplace MCI
(www.internetmci.com). But while these other sites use their
generators in-house to build catalogs from materials provided by
clients, Webgen‚Äôs generator can be used interactively by anyone with
a modem and a copy of Netscape.</p>

  <p>This will (lower the cost)[3] of putting a catalog online by, say,
90%. It also means that our (volume is not limited by the number of
clients we can serve personally)[4]. We would be a (software
company)[5], (not a service company)[6].</p>

</blockquote>

